            <p class="eyebrow">When to call</p>
            <h2>When to call for emergency drain cleaning</h2>
            <p>If your drain problem is <strong>causing water damage, creating a health risk, or completely stopping you from using your home or business normally</strong>, that is an emergency. Here are the most common scenarios where you should not wait.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Sewage backups</h3><p>Wastewater backing up into your showers, tubs, sinks, or toilets is a serious health hazard that needs immediate attention.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Multiple drains clogged at once</h3><p>When more than one drain backs up at once, it is usually a sign of a main sewer line blockage, not just a simple clog.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Overflowing fixtures</h3><p>Sinks or toilets that will not stop overflowing can cause severe water damage to your floors and walls fast.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>04</span><div><h3>Persistent sewage odors</h3><p>A strong, lingering sewage smell coming from your drains often signals a serious blockage or a broken pipe somewhere in the line.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>05</span><div><h3>Sudden, total blockage</h3><p>If water in your home has stopped draining completely, that is an emergency. Do not wait.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>06</span><div><h3>Gurgling drains or pipes</h3><p>Unusual gurgling sounds when you run water or flush the toilet can indicate a blockage is building up and about to get worse.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>07</span><div><h3>Flooded basements or standing water</h3><p>Water pooling in your basement or yard can point to a main line issue and lead to structural damage and mold if left unaddressed.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>08</span><div><h3>Recurring or stubborn clogs</h3><p>When plungers and DIY drain cleaners are not cutting it anymore, it is time to call in the experts before the problem causes permanent damage.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>09</span><div><h3>Critical business disruptions</h3><p>For restaurants, hotels, and other businesses, a drain problem can result in lost revenue and customer dissatisfaction. We are here to get your doors open again quickly.</p></div></article>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-top:var(--sp-4)">If you are unsure, give Honest Drain a call. We are available 24/7, 365 days a year to answer your questions and respond immediately. It is always better to reach out early than wait and risk a costly problem.</p>
