            <p class="eyebrow">FAQs</p>
            <h2>Emergency drain cleaning FAQs</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-list">
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">How quickly can Honest Drain respond to a drain emergency?</button><div><p>In most cases, an Honest Drain technician can be at your door the same day you call, often within just a few hours. We are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, including weekends and holidays, so you are never waiting until the next business day to get help.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">What should I do while waiting for a technician to arrive?</button><div><p>Stop using all water in your home. If you can, locate your main water shut-off valve and turn it off. Keep people and pets away from areas with standing water. Remove excess water if safe to do so. Do not use chemical drain cleaners, as these can make certain blockages harder to clear.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Will you just clear the clog, or will you figure out what caused it?</button><div><p>We do both. We use video camera inspection technology to identify the root cause, whether that is grease buildup, hair and debris accumulation, a foreign object, tree root intrusion, or a collapsed pipe section. Understanding why the emergency happened is the only way to prevent it from happening again.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Can a clogged drain cause damage to my home if I wait?</button><div><p>Yes, and it can happen faster than most people expect. A backed-up drain puts pressure on your pipes and can lead to sewage overflow, water damage to floors and walls, mold growth, and structural damage. The longer a blockage sits unaddressed, the more expensive the fix tends to become.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Do you offer emergency drain cleaning for businesses?</button><div><p>Absolutely. We work with commercial properties of all sizes and understand that getting your doors back open quickly is the priority. Our team is equipped to handle high-volume commercial drain systems and responds with the same urgency as any residential call.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

